   489	## Out of Scope
   490	
   491	- Any Dockerfile for an EDEN service (`task-store-server`,
   492	  `orchestrator`, etc.). 10b.
   493	- Any `PostgresStore` Python code. Lands when its consumer lands —
   494	  10b.
   495	- Any blob storage Python code. 10d.
   496	- The `setup-experiment` script. 10c.
   497	- Gitea admin user / API token bootstrap. 10c.
   498	- Production-grade secrets management. The `.env` pattern is
   499	  developer-grade; production deployments override.
   500	- Compose overrides for the e2e test. 10e may add a `compose.test.yaml`.
   501	- Branch protection update to require `compose-smoke`. Deferred to
   502	  a follow-up after the job is proven stable.
   503	
   504	## Known Risks / Things to Watch
   505	
   506	- **GitHub Actions Docker version drift.** `ubuntu-latest` updates
   507	  Docker periodically; Compose v2 syntax we use (`--wait`,
   508	  `--wait-timeout`, `name:` top-level field, no `version:` key) all
   509	  require Docker Compose v2.20+. As of April 2026 `ubuntu-latest`
   510	  ships v2.27+, so we have margin, but if the runner ever
   511	  downgrades the smoke job will break loudly. We don't pin Docker
   512	  in CI because GitHub controls that.
   513	- **Gitea startup is slow.** First boot of `gitea/gitea:1.22.6-rootless`
   514	  takes 15-25 seconds on a cold runner. The healthcheck
   515	  `start_period: 30s` covers this; if it ever proves flaky,
   516	  the next move is bumping to 60s rather than reducing the test.
   517	- **Image-pin staleness.** `postgres:16.6-alpine` and
   518	  `gitea/gitea:1.22.6-rootless` will be superseded. We pin
   519	  deliberately; Phase 10e or a dedicated bump PR refreshes both
   520	  together when the next Compose round lands.
   521	- **Port-collision regret.** Defaults of 5433 / 3001 / 2222 sidestep
   522	  the most common collisions but a developer running their own
   523	  Gitea on 3001 will hit one. The README's Troubleshooting section
   524	  documents the `.env` overrides; no other mitigation is worth it.
   525	- **`.env.example` rotation.** The dev-only secrets in `.env.example`
   526	  are intentionally weak. If a future contributor copies them to a
   527	  real deployment they're in trouble. The README's Quickstart
   528	  section labels the values as throwaway; we additionally make
   529	  `POSTGRES_PASSWORD`, `GITEA_SECRET_KEY`, `GITEA_INTERNAL_TOKEN`
   530	  required-with-error-on-missing in `compose.yaml`, so production
   531	  users who delete `.env` get a clear failure rather than silently
   532	  inheriting weak defaults.
   533	- **Compose project-name leakage.** The `name: eden-reference`
   534	  field means volumes get the prefix `eden-reference_`. If a
   535	  developer also runs the predecessor's direvo monolith via
   536	  Compose, project names won't collide. If they ever rename our
   537	  `name:` field, every `docker volume ls` reference and every
   538	  `compose down -v` invocation that targets historical data will
   539	  miss the old volumes. We document the project name in the README.
   540	- **Compose v1 (`docker-compose`) users.** v1 is EOL since June
   541	  2023. Some legacy systems still ship it; those users will see
   542	  syntax errors on `name:` and `--wait`. The README's prerequisites
   543	  section names `docker compose` v2.20+ explicitly. No backcompat
   544	  shim.
   545	
   546	## Files to Reference
   547	
   548	- `direvo/Dockerfile` — predecessor's container shape, kept for
   549	  10b context but **not** copied for 10a.
   550	- `docs/roadmap.md` — Phase 10 unit definitions.
   551	- `reference/README.md` — current "Compose: Phase 10" placeholder
   552	  that this chunk updates.
   553	- The Postgres image docs (`hub.docker.com/_/postgres`) for
